    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long guns used in England in the late 16th century for military purposes, as they can be fired without rest. They were a newer form of the harquebus, but were not used after the Civil War. They were generally sized larger than the harquebus and smaller than the musket.</Note_Text>
